 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a5c9d607",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# RAG System QuickStart\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to use the unified `RAGService` to build an index and run queries with the optimized **Two-Stage Retrieval** (Summary -> LLM Rerank -> Detail).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Prerequisites:**\n",
    "- Ensure `.env` is configured with your API keys and Database URL.\n",
    "- Ensure Docker containers (Postgres/pgvector) are running."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "init-setup",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add project root to sys.path\n",
    "repo_root = Path.cwd().resolve().parent\n",
    "if str(repo_root) not in sys.path:\n",
    "    sys.path.insert(0, str(repo_root))\n",
    "\n",
    "from rag_system.config import RAGConfig\n",
    "from rag_system.rag_service import RAGService\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load configuration\n",
    "load_dotenv(repo_root / ".env")\n",
    "config = RAGConfig.from_env()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Override for testing (Optional)\n",
    "# config.summary_top_k = 10\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Project Root: {repo_root}\")\n",
    "print(f\"DB Connection: {bool(config.conn_string)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Service Config: summary_top_k={config.summary_top_k}, detail_top_k={config.detail_top_k}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "indexing-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Indexing Documents\n",
    "\n",
    "This step reads files from `data/converted_md`, splits them into chunks (Parent/Child), and stores them in Postgres (Vector) and LocalFileStore (Content)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "run-indexing",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "service = RAGService(config)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define data directory\n",
    "data_dir = repo_root / \"data/converted_md\"\n",
    "\n",
    "if not data_dir.exists():\n",
    "    print(f\"Data directory not found: {data_dir}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(f\"Indexing files from: {data_dir}\")\n",
    "    # Indexing (Set clear_index=True to wipe DB before indexing)\n",
    "    # service.clear_index() \n",
    "    # service = RAGService(config) # Re-init if cleared\n",
    "    \n",
    "    results = service.index_directory(data_dir, pattern=\"*.md\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Indexing Results: {results}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "querying-section",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Querying (Two-Stage Retrieval)\n",
    "\n",
    "Test the retrieval logic. This bypasses the Agent generation and strictly tests if the RAG system can find the correct document.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Logic:**\n",
    "1. **Vector Search**: Find top `summary_top_k` (10) chunks.\n",
    "2. **LLM Rerank**: Ask LLM to pick the most relevant one.\n",
    "3. **Fetch Parent**: Retrieve the full context of the winner."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "run-query",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize Service (if not already)\n",
    "service = RAGService(config)\n",
    "\n",
    "query = \"軍人權益事件處理法第15條規定了什麼？\"\n",
    "print(f\"Query: {query}\\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "docs = service.query(query)\n",
    "\n",
    "if docs:\n",
    "    print(f\"✅ Found {len(docs)} document(s):\n\")\n",
    "    for i, doc in enumerate(docs, 1):\n",
    "        source = doc.metadata.get(\"source\", \"Unknown\")\n",
    "        print(f\"--- Document {i} ({source}) ---\")\n",
    "        print(doc.page_content[:500] + \"... [truncated]\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"❌ No documents found.\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
